3.You are given an integer array arr[]. Your task is to find the smallest positive number missing from the array.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    public int missingNumber(int[] arr) {
        HashSet<Integer>s=new HashSet<>();
        for(int n:arr){
            if(n>0){s.add(n);}}
            int a=1;
            while(s.contains(a)){
                a++;
            }  
     return a;
    }
}

Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/smallest-positive-missing-number-1587115621/1
4.You are given an array arr[] of non-negative integers. You have to move all the zeros in the array to the right end while maintaining the relative order of the non-zero elements. The operation must be performed in place, meaning you should not use extra space for another array.
Platform : GeeksForGeeks
SOURCE CODE : class Solution {
    void pushZerosToEnd(int[] arr) {
        int j=0;
      for(int i=0;i<arr.length;i++){
          if(arr[i]!=0){
              int temp=arr[i];
              arr[i]=arr[j];
              arr[j]=temp; j++;
      }
      }  
    }
}
Link : https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/problems/move-all-zeroes-to-end-of-array0751/1
5.Given the root of a binary tree, return all root-to-leaf paths in any order.
A leaf is a node with no children.
Platform :Leetcode
SOURCE CODE : public class TreeNode {
   int val;
      TreeNode left;
     TreeNode right;
      TreeNode() {}
      TreeNode(int val) { this.val = val; }
      TreeNode(int val, TreeNode left, TreeNode right) {
          this.val = val;
          this.left = left;
          this.right = right;
      }
  }
class Solution {
    public List<String> binaryTreePaths(TreeNode root) {
          List<String> li=new  ArrayList<>();
          if(root==null){return li;}
          treepath(root,"",li);
          return li;}
           void treepath(TreeNode root,String path,List<String>li){
            if(root==null){return ;}
            path=path+root.val;
            if(root.left==null && root.right==null){
                li.add(path);return;
            }
                  path+="->";
                  treepath(root.left,path,li);
                  treepath(root.right,path,li);
           }
}
Link : https://leetcode.com/problems/binary-tree-paths/
